Tour and Travel MERN Stack Project
A secure MERN Stack web application for managing tour bookings. Built with MongoDB, Express.js, React.js, Node.js, and TypeScript, providing users with an easy way to plan and book tours.

Setup

1. Clone the Repo
   bash
   Copy
   Edit
   git clone https://github.com/Anuzzzzzzzz/security/tree/final
   cd tour-and-travel
2. Frontend Setup
   bash
   Copy
   Edit
   cd client
   npm install
   npm run dev
3. Backend Setup
   bash
   Copy
   Edit
   cd server
   npm install
   npm run dev
4. Environment Variables
   Create a .env file in the backend directory with:

plaintext
Copy
Edit
PORT=5000
MONGO_URI=your-mongo-uri
Security Features
JWT Authentication for secure user sessions.
bcryptjs for password hashing.
Helmet.js to secure HTTP headers.
CORS to restrict API access to trusted domains.
Rate Limiting to prevent brute-force attacks.
This README provides a brief overview and instructions to get the project up and running with security measures.

